    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-halloumi-burger-with-fries-and-peri-nnaise/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into quarters</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> into quarters</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open with the side of a knife and remove the skin</p><p>Cut your<strong> red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop roughly</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-halloumi-burger-with-fries-and-peri-nnaise/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong>, <strong>crushed garlic </strong>and<strong> shallot quarters </strong>with a small splash of <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water </strong>and cook for 5 min or until slightly softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-halloumi-burger-with-fries-and-peri-nnaise/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, transfer the <strong>softened</strong> <strong>shallot</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chopped pepper </strong>to a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Reserve the pan with the <strong>remaining pepper </strong>for later</p><p>Add your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the food processor with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> white wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and<strong> </strong>blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>peri-peri sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-halloumi-burger-with-fries-and-peri-nnaise/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>halloumi</strong> in half, lengthways (like you're slicing a burger bun!)</p><p>Return the reserved pan with the pepper to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> sliced halloumi</strong> with 1 tbsp of <strong>peri-peri sauce </strong>per person<strong> </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until the halloumi is browned and the reserved pepper is tender \u2013 this is your <strong>pepper & peri-peri halloumi</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-halloumi-burger-with-fries-and-peri-nnaise/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>remaining peri-peri sauce</strong> with a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>peri-nnaise</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-halloumi-burger-with-fries-and-peri-nnaise/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half (if required!)</p><p>Add the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>brioche</strong> to a large baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through</p><p>Wash then remove 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>leaf </strong>from the<strong> lettuce</strong> per person, pat it dry with kitchen paper and set aside</p><p>Chop the<strong> inner core[s]</strong> into quarters, lengthways</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-halloumi-burger-with-fries-and-peri-nnaise/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To build, layer the <strong>toasted brioche base </strong>with a <strong>lettuce leaf</strong>, a wedge of <strong>pepper</strong> and the<strong> peri-peri halloumi</strong></p><p>Dollop over the <strong>peri-nnaise </strong>and top with a <strong>toasted brioche lid</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>peri-peri halloumi burger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>peri-peri halloumi burger </strong>with the<strong> fries</strong>, <strong>lettuce wedges </strong>and any <strong>remaining peri-nnaise</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
